FT  03 FEB 94 / Tourist spending hits record Pounds 8.4bn
Spending by overseas visitors to the UK increased by 15 per cent to a record
Pounds 8.4bn in the first 11 months of last year, the British Tourist
Authority said yesterday.
This compares with the Pounds 7.9bn spent in the whole of 1992.
The number of visitors in the first 11 months of last year increased by 5
per cent to 17.9m, also a record.
